history.content: Haven't taken either classes, but from looking at the syllibi, 184 and 194-26 are sort of "inverse" classics. 184 being a graphics class, is going from some idealized description of a scene to an image, where 194-26 is a computer vision class, which is learning to understand a scene from an image. I would recommend taking a look at both syllabi for more detail, but there will not be significant overlap beyond the pinhole camera module and probably discussion of colors.

I've always wanted to take 194-26 (computational photography) but since I'm planning to study abroad next fall (as a senior), I probably won't have the chance to take it. However I'm taking CS 184 this Spring and I'm wondering how much both courses overlap and how self studying 194-26 would be having already taken CS 184.
history.subject: 184 VS 194-26
